          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for public or private recitation or prayer and worship (pūjā) of the Great Goddess of Hinduism, sometimes referred to simply as Devī (goddess). Text praises a thousand different names of the goddess and is from a larger work known as the Rudrayāmala, a Tantric Śaiva work.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Devīsahasranāmastotra</title>
              <title type="vernacular">देवीसहस्रनामस्तोत्र</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīrudrayāmale naṃdikeśvaramaheśasaṃvāde devīsahasranāmastotraṃ samāptaṃ // śrīmahālakṣmīpriyatāṃ mama // śubham astu sarvajagataḥ // śrīrasta // (f. 12v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
